        <headline>Severe Thunderstorm Warning issued June 27 at 5:14PM MDT until June 27 at 6:15PM MDT by NWS Glasgow MT</headline>
        <description>SVRGGW

The National Weather Service in Glasgow has issued a

* Severe Thunderstorm Warning for...
Southeastern Phillips County in northeastern Montana...
Eastern Petroleum County in northeastern Montana...
Southwestern Garfield County in northeastern Montana...

* Until 615 PM MDT.

* At 514 PM MDT, severe thunderstorms were located along a line
extending from 15 miles west of U L Bend Rec Area to 12 miles south
of Crooked Creek Rec Area to 13 miles east of Flatwillow, moving
east at 30 mph.

HAZARD...60 mph wind gusts.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect damage to roofs, siding, and trees.

* Locations impacted include...
Sand Springs, Devils Creek Rec Area, U L Bend Rec Area, Edwards,
Mosby, Crooked Creek Rec Area, Brusett, Steve Fork, and Cat Creek.
</description>
        <instruction>For your protection move to an interior room on the lowest floor of a
building.</instruction>
